						<summary>

						<p>Two fragments of a broken pillar set up at two different places inside the village.</p>						

						<p>Agga[pa] of Mahābali-kula.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to records a gift of 50 <hi rend="italic">maṟutus</hi> of land <hi rend="italic">(pannasa)</hi> to Uḍugugaṇdlya and to Paḷḷa Pishṭamayya of Alikoṇḍala by Bejayitāyya. Refers to Rattaguḍis. In characters of about the 9th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
